程序包 ca.mcgill.ecse211.project

类 Resources

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.mcgill.ecse211.project.Resources
  • public class Resources
extends java.lang.Object
    Class for static resources (things that stay the same throughout the entire program execution), like constants and hardware.

    Use these resources in other files by adding this line at the top (see examples):

    import static ca.mcgill.ecse211.project.Resources.*;

      • println

        public static void println​(java.lang.Object... objects)
        Print method that prepends the team number before the object(s) to be printed, separated by spaces, followed by a newline at the end. This method must be used instead of System.out.println(), to ensure console output can be traced to the team. Note that printing constantly (eg, in a loop) can be inefficient and impact robot performance. Example usage/output:
        println("Moving to " + waypoint(i)); 
        Team 01: Moving to (1, 3).

      • errPrintln

        public static void errPrintln​(java.lang.Object... objects)
        Print method for errors that prepends the team number before the object(s) to be printed, separated by spaces, followed by a newline at the end. This method must be used instead of System.err.println(), to ensure console output can be traced to the team. Example usage/output:
        println("Moving to " + waypoint(i)); 
        Team 01: Moving to (1, 3).

      • print

        public static void print​(java.lang.Object... objects)
        Print method that prepends the team number before the object(s) to be printed, separated by spaces, without a newline at the end. This method must be used instead of System.out.print(), to ensure console output can be traced to the team.

      • customPrint

        public static void customPrint​(boolean printNewlines,
                               java.io.PrintStream ps,
                               java.lang.Object... objects)
        Custom print method to allow customization while always prepending the team number before items to be printed.
        参数:
        printNewlines - if this is true, the printed output will end with a newline
        ps - the PrintStream, usually System.out or System.err
        objects - the item(s) to be printed
